<dl id="n12124d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12124d">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12124d"> 124(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ~ tomb for bargain)</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">This shows us that they believed in a world to come. Everything tends to prove that the worship of the dead formed a great part of their religion, and that certain ceremonies and their <mark>bargains always took place beside the tombs</mark>. <small> Zacharie Le Rouzic, <a name="MMCL" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#MMCL"><cite title="source">The Megalithic Monuments of Carnac and Locmariaquer</cite></a> (1908) 34</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c12127k" href="c12all.htm#c12127k">VI.C.12:127(k)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
